Description:
At Globant, we are working to make the world a better place, one step at a time. We enhance business development and enterprise solutions to prepare them for a digital future. With a diverse and talented team present in more than 30 countries, we are strategic partners to leading global companies in their business process transformation.

As part of our continued growth, we are expanding our presence in Germany and seeking professionals who are ready to thrive in a fast-paced, evolving environment. We are looking for proactive, passionate, and versatile individuals who thrive in dynamic environments and are eager to make an impact from day one. Here, you will find extended career opportunities, a collaborative culture, and the chance to work on innovative, high-impact projects.

We are currently on the lookout for a Senior Data Scientist who shares our passion for innovation and change and who will be part of our Data & AI Studio, where we define and build the best data products and strategies to meet our Clients' needs.

This role is critical to helping our business partners evolve and adapt to consumers' personalized expectations in this new technological era.

What will help you succeed:


Fluency in English and German (C1 - Advanced);
8+ years of hands-on experience in data science, machine learning, or AI roles;
Proven track record of leading complex, high-impact projects from ideation to deployment;
Deep expertise in machine learning frameworks (e.g., TensorFlow, PyTorch, scikit-learn) and statistical analysis;
Proficient in programming languages such as Python, R, and SQL; experience with big data technologies (e.g., Spark, Hadoop) is a plus;
Strong understanding of data engineering principles, MLOps, and cloud platforms (AWS, GCP, or Azure);
Excellent problem-solving skills, critical thinking, and the ability to make data-driven decisions;
Outstanding communication and interpersonal skills; able to influence senior stakeholders and work across disciplines;
Experience mentoring or managing technical teams is highly desirable.



At Globant, you will join a community of innovators, creators, and problem-solvers who are passionate about driving meaningful change. We believe in empowering our people to grow both personally and professionally, offering extensive learning opportunities, career development pathways, and the chance to work on some of the most exciting projects in the industry. If you are looking for an environment where your contributions are valued and your potential can truly flourish, Globant is the right place for you.

At Globant, we believe in fostering a diverse and inclusive workplace where everyone feels valued and respected. We are an Equal Opportunity Employer committed to creating a thriving and inclusive environment for all employees and candidates, regardless of race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, age, disability, veteran status, or other legally protected characteristics. If you need any assistance or accommodation due to a disability, please let us know by applying through our Career Site or contacting your assigned Recruiter.

We may use AI and machine learning technologies in our recruitment process. Compensation is determined based on skills, qualifications, experience, and location. In addition to competitive salaries, we offer a comprehensive benefits package. Learn more about our commitment to diversity and inclusion and Globant's benefits.
